text: In the bone- marrow (BM) aspiration, blasts accounted for 88.1% of ANCs, which were positive for CD9 and CD10 on flow cytometry. Measurements of serum tumor markers showed elevated level of Cyfra21-1: 4.77 ng/mL, NSE: 19.60 ng/mL, and SCCA: 2.58 ng/mL. Immunohistochemical staining showed positive staining for CK5/6, P40, and negative staining for TTF-1 and weakly positive staining for ALK.
